name: Toko Seniman
address: Jl. PB. Sudirman, Ruko Sudirman Agung Blok A-49, Dauh Puri Klod, Denpasar Barat, Denpasar City, Bali 80225, Indonesia
review 1:
My friend told me to stop by and had a different experience to sip a coffee. And that's right!
I chose their affogato, and got an extra bold cold brew from their blend arabica's beans.
The Affogato just perfect as i could imagine, a bitter sweet.
For the pastry, you must try their beef sausage roll.

At their 2nd floor, their have art space with a lot vinyl collection that you can choose to play. A good ambience just to hangout with beloved one
review 2:
Charming coffee shop! Love the Cotcha, it‚Äôs the matcha espresso on ice‚Äî a perfect blend of robust espresso and the earthy notes of matcha. The way it‚Äôs served alongside a separate shot of espresso, a tiny cookie, and a glass of water all on an elegant long tray, adds a touch of sophistication.

Also love the choice of furniture, Marigold buds on each table, and the beautifully displayed selection of coffee beans and coffeemaker apparatuses add to an artsy ambiance. Despite the cinnamon roll being a bit salty for my taste, the overall experience was wonderful. I would recommend this unique coffee spot to friends for its exceptional fusion of flavors, and charming atmosphere! ‚ù§Ô∏è
review 3: Nice place, nice vibes. U can take the coffee maker class. Unique how they served the coffee. The first time I got here i didn't see the sign, because it was quite small and not too obvious. Inside the shophouse complex. U can work here, chitchat with friends or colleagues. Definitely recommended!
review 4:
They are expert on coffee, nuff said.

Also, check out their record store on 2nd floor. They do showcase of their collection every week, and their collection is tasteful.
review 5:
Visited here during free time, open till night but their collaboration store located on the second floor only open until around 7 pm.
Friendly and heartwarming staff.
Lots of coffee beans (grind) are available from around Indonesia. Brewed well.
Their ready to go coffee was delicious.
They also offered meal.

name: Starbucks Sudirman
address: Jl. Jend. Sudirman Jl. P.B. Sudirman No.6, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: One of my fave Starbucks place. Cozy, relaxing place, not crowded. The ambience is suitable for chill or work from cafe. Friendly baristas. The place also have  patio for smoking area. Parking area available for car and motorbike. You must try spicy tuna bread, it's so delicious.
review 2: The place is easy to find. It's quite spacious than other Starbucks tho. The parking guy is annoying, he disappeared, but suddenly made an appearance when I started my motorbike and charged 2k when Bali as a fixed rate of parking which is 1k.
review 3: Starbucks Sudirman is located on PB Sudirman Street, near Udayana University. This Starbucks is large enough and provides indoor and outdoor space. The ambience is so cool and i think it's really suitable for you who look for a place to work or study. You can also get some talks with your friend here. Their interior feels so warm yet classy with smooth melody in the air. They also provides baby chair for customer who bring kids. Beside that, their parking area is really large and it's enough for 10 cars and 15 motorcycles. I cant count how many times i come there because i really really often to come there for doing my worküòçüòçüòç
review 4:
Coffe is standard Starbucks but what makes this Starbucks stands out is the service and the place! It‚Äôs so comfy for studying or even just for a coffee, great decor even not surpasses starbucks dewata but still great!
Plenty of parking and you‚Äôll need to pay for parking, idk why, capitalist I guess.
review 5: Spacious, comfortable for working space as any other Starbucks, cheerful baristas, so so coffee~

name: Masjid An-Nur - Denpasar
address: Jl. Diponegoro No.192, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80114, Indonesia
review 1: Masya Allah tabarakallah, the mosque is beautifully arranged and the shoe rack is complete with the letters of the alphabet, the car park is safe, the prayer place on the top floor is very cool and comfortable ‚ù§Ô∏è
review 2: 2 floors, below for female, above for male. Spacious, clean, nice and comfy.
review 3: Clean, large, and comfortable. It's easy to notice, located at the side of the road, and there're limited parking space. It has great facilities such as free drinking water, books, information boards, sarong, mukena. At 1st floor, there're women's prayer area, men's prayer area, and also we can take a break of have some rest in this area. The main prayer area, for men, is in the 2nd floor.
review 4: Dont forget to pray here. Good and nice

name: Twenty One Coffee&Eatery
address: Jl. Batu Sari III No.6, Renon, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1:
A hidden gem in town! You need to explore the alleys and some housing areas to get there. I really recommend you to open your Google Maps to find this cafe.

First, I would like to review their food. Overall it had standard taste with big platting style (the portion was standard i think, not that big). The one I concerned for their food is about the serving time. It took so long times..i think the serving time took approximately 40-60 minutes (?) So please dont expect they would serve your meals that fastü´†

Second, I would review the ambience and decoration. I admit their ambience was really homey so you would feel comfy while visiting this cafe. The decoration was quite minimalis yet beautiful so there would be several spots for you instagramable photosüëç

Third, I think they need to train their waiters about the product knowledge and customer management skills. When I ordered some meals and asked them about the menu‚Äôs characteristic, they couldn‚Äôt explain it and always asking the other coworkers. They were also lil bit slow in serving customers and it made their works not effectiveüôèüèª

Ps : maybe the management should provide parking sign in the parking area so the customers wouldn‚Äôt be confused to park their vehicles
review 2: Nice nice cafe. Delicious Americano, I think it's a specialty coffee. Rice bowl blac pepper is perfectly spicy. There is a slight confusion with parking: you need to install a more explicit parking sign. Clean, quiet. Our morning order arrived quickly.
review 3: This place is so cozy. Love the atmosphere of the place.

name: BSH Coffee House
address: Jl. Serma Made Pil No.18, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80114, Indonesia
review 1:
Great place to chill or escape for a moment in Denpasar. The fish pond with its big fish will give you a fabulous experience.
The coffee is also great, you can choose the bean that you like for your coffee.
review 2:
The best place for coffee.... they have 3 different mixed various bean coffee special for you!!

Minus is don't have space parking for car and one more until now they didn't have also for heavy food only snacks food.

So enjoy the coffee and ambience with friendly staff....
review 3: I like the architecture of this coffee shop, although I was not really pleased with the open space because it need extra works to clean from dust and also water dripping (from rain or their drainage). The indoor space little bit too tight so the customers would sit very near to each other, not comfortable enough to talk with friends as it could be heard by the other customers. But the good things are the coffee and sandwich were tasteful for me, and the staff (or baristas) are so friendly and hilarious.
review 4: amazing place with unique design, comfortable vibe and delicious coffee. The staff is friendly very nice explain to us there‚Äôs 3 type of coffee beans. Definitely back againüòò
review 5: Great architecture and concept in the city centre. Very warm ambience especially in their garden. Such a good place to get afternoon coffee. But they need to improve the quality of the coffee. For a coffee lover, i tasted their coffee is bland (americano was only served with 1 shot of espresso, ask for extra shot for better kick).

name: SAGA Coffee Bali
address: Jl. Serma Tugir No.5, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80113, Indonesia
review 1:
Very cozy. Love the atmosphere. My cappuccino was excellent.

They‚Äôve gotta couple guitars complete with strings. One was even in tune and had a capo with pick.

The service was friendly. No space for cars to park. But that fits the neighborhood vibe.

The only negative is the building is showing it‚Äôs age. Doesn‚Äôt seem to be much maintenance. Also, wish they‚Äôd get rid of that hideous orange cone in front lol.
review 2:
found out bout this place from my bf's tiktok, and the first thought was legit "let's try this place out."
it turned out better than our expectations, a solid 9/10 and would definitely come again. the service and the atmosphere were just perfect to us!
review 3:
It was another fine experience to have a coffee here; open early morning with great outdoor seating. Narrow space but still cozy. Recommended to only use bike/ motorcycle here due to their limited parking space in front of and around the shop.
Friendly staff and barista that serve well. The menu was written on detailed explanation for new customer.
review 4:
Ambience : 8/10
Taste : 9/10
Price : Rp.16.000 - Rp.45.000

Recommended,
Drink : Matcha by SAGA & SAGA Honey Hatchi.

For Danish & Pastry : available in the morning ( Limited Stock )
review 5: Great place to grab a cup coffee and some snacks. The prices are affordable, nice and cozy environment. Great place to hang out with your friends.

name: Dunkin Donuts Sudirman
address: Jl. Jend. Sudirman No.4A, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: I missed Dunkin Donuts from my time living in Chicago where they were huge .  This shop is conveniently located next to my bank HSBC which is nice because I can wait here if I'm early for an appointment or I can drop by after one.  If brims back good memories of my time in the US .  It's very quiet here as they don't get much business which is not good for them but nice for a place to relax .  The staff is very nice , they even opened up early for me once when I came too early .  Nicely air conditioned and the food is as I remembered.  I hour they get more business during the afternoon as I would hate for this place to close down . You can get a dunkin donuts card to get dunkin too but I don't come here often enough to make it worth my while .
review 2:
Thank God this place is open again since the last time it closed during pandemicüòä

Always love their iced chocolate, good company to any of their donuts. The staffs are friendly.

Nice place to hang bcs its not crowded. Also you can work from here too, they got high speed wifi & power socket on every table, so no worries.
review 3: A bit interesting experience I had here.. the lady at the front desk wasn‚Äôt paying much attention to me when I was trying to order food. She was on her phone a lot and took really long to help me with my order‚Ä¶ it still tasted great but it wasn‚Äôt a true Bali experience
review 4:
Same as all dunkin donuts, comfortable to sit there at the window

UPDATE (13/10/2020)

review 5: the worst dunkin donuts joint, been to every dunkin donuts in denpasar and this is by far the worst, the upstair air conditioning not working, when it does work it's not really that cool as if they set the temperature high for whatever reason, staff not smiling when they talk to you, and one day they didn't even make their tiramisu collata the right way-it was tasteless, and they never really clean the tables upstairs, dunno about the tables downstairs though.

name: Cindra Kos
address: Gg. Mandau No.11 A, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia

name: Wedang Ronde & Angsle Mas Parwok
address: Dauh Puri Klod, Denpasar Barat, Denpasar City, Bali 80113, Indonesia
review 1:
For me, everything is just so so. Nothing special but the line here is always long. They have Wedang Ronde, Angsle, Sekoteng, Wedang Jahe, Cilok, Pukis, Ketan.

I was interested in their Ketan so I bought two portions. I expected it to taste like Ketan as in Mango Sticky Rice but nope. It's quite salty for Ketan. Could've been better if they cook it with coconut milk.
review 2: The crowdness of this warung makes me curious how the taste of their menu. I usually ordered Angsle when it comes to warung ronde but I was full already so I only tried theirSekoteng. IMO it taste so-so, the ginger tea tastes too mild to me. There's no proper seat, just a short chair as the table and sit on the floor. Next time i‚Äôll try the angsle.
review 3:
Keep it up!
Broth could be a bit spicier but the soy milk is sooo fresh and taste homemade!!
Would definitely come back

Cilok is good. Very chewy
review 4:
i‚Äôve never know what ‚Äúangsle‚Äù is before, and this place is already there for a quite long time and i never had in mind to stop by. then when me and my gf passed this place and saw so many people going here, we‚Äôre so curious and try to taste it. when we tried, the taste is very good, my gf try their angsle and i have my wedang ronde.
you guys should take a visit here, very recommended to have this drink while the night is cold, this could warm youüòâ
review 5:
Best ronde ginger in Denpasar.
Best service from the workers.

name: Ruang Terbuka Hijau Universitas Udayana
address: 86G9+WH5 Universitas Udayana, Jl. P.B. Sudirman, Dauh Puri, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia

address: Jl. Tukad Banyu Sari No.8, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80113, Indonesia

name: Coto Makassar Sudirman
address: Jalan PB Sudirman Ruko Sudirman Agung Blok F No 16, Dauh Puri Klod, Denpasar Barat, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80113, Indonesia
review 1: Such an under rated hidden gem in Bali that I honestly loved. I wouldn't have gotten lucky enough to stumble upon this place if it weren't for my partner and his mum who's been going to this place for years. Cannot wait to come back for the Coto Makassar Daging and the Es Pisang Ijo dessert!
review 2: A rare find in Bali, a legit and delicious Coto Makassar! One bowl has enough meat to share with another person. It was 30k without rice. Yummy!
review 3: It's been my favorite meat soup from Makassar for a long time since I have been in Bali. Coming back recently for lunch, nothing changes just price inflation.
review 4:
This is a fantastic place to eat something completely different. No, not the Indonesian wife speciality that is Coto Makassar, but the sublime Konro.
This is a beef rib or two in a stew. Hit sauce added separately to taste, you need hands to gnaw the meat from the bone, tender and juicy. It could be a fabulous Irish stew, if you added potatoes and carrots! Not too be missed.
review 5: I have tried several coto makasaar in Bali, and definitely this place is not for my palette. Though I respect all the people who tried to bring their cultural food to Bali for everyone to try. But I still prefer the one at the Legian street.. yet I enjoy their coto makassar and es pisang ijo, still it‚Äôs not for me.. sorry..üôèüèª

name: Loving Hut
address: Pertokoan Sudirman Agung B 12A, 80234, Jl. Jend. Sudirman, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80232, Indonesia
review 1: One of my most favorite vegan restaurant in Bali! We ordered their famous Nasi Campur and seaweed tofu and we really enjoyed it! Semuanya enakkk! And we are full bcs the portion was quite big for petite me. Staf ramah dan helpful. Looks like they had regular customers here. Definitely will come back here utk cobain menu lainnya. Thank you for the service! Keep up the good work!
review 2: Enjoyable lunch while saving the planet. The food was tasty but I was disappointed that the bakso was sold out. Service was good.
review 3: Hood food and friendly service.. the also have packets of v3gan cookies!! We had 2 mains and 4 sides between 2 of us and including the vegan cookies it cost 142k. Very good price for money. Would recommend üòÅ
review 4:
Good location. Good service. Extensive menu. Most importantly, delicious vegetarian food - ingredients are fresh and vegetables are not over cooked. Seasoning is mild, so it's not overpowering. Recommended.

2 things I would like to suggest to management: 1. Please inform your staff to not laugh, shout, and chat very loudly, as the restaurant is quite small, it can be disturbing. 2. Please review and improve cleanliness at the restaurant, because when I ate there yesterday, I spotted a small cockroach on the table.
review 5: The staffs were friendly and food was good but the balinese veggie was a little bit salty. The satay and soup were great! Portion was great with the price

name: J.J Apartments - Denpasar Bali
address: Jl. Batusari No.2x, Dangin Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: Nice people, but the building is rotting and nobody cares. Since 2 months the ceiling of my bathroom looks really bad.I can‚Äôt speak a lot of bahasa and the very friendly manager doesn‚Äôt speak English. So my bathroom and kitchen keep on rotting and producing dangerous mushrooms on the walls.
review 2: Quiet, convenient, and relatively inexpensive. It has all the basic amenities such as hot shower, local/international tv channels, free wifi, small  kitchen, altogether with a spacious bathroom. Electric bills are paid independently using token cards, and it also keeps a small swimming pool inside. Apart from the fact that it might be far from common tourist sites, it is still a pleasant home.
review 3: I've been lived in JJ for 3 months with my cat. I have very private room under the stairs, and so comfortable. All the facilities is here, wifi, hot and cold water, TV with international channels, and of courses pet friendly.
review 4: Pretty convenient. Good for sleep, close to the city center. Water heater is not working
review 5: Beautiful enough, and I really like the service there

name: AB CAFE BALI
address: Jl. Serma Made Pil No.55, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80113, Indonesia

name: Savayas Yoga Studio & Caf√©

name: Rumah Makan Simpang Ampek Panjer
address: Jl. Waturenggong No.126, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80225, Indonesia
review 1: An interesting restaurant which specialises in Sumatran food, the beef rendang is well worth it, unfortunately the rest of the food is rather bland
review 2: If you are looking for the best 'nasi padang' then here you have to go. Trust me!
review 3: Their food tastes good. The serving size is adequate. As for the price, it's a bit high compared to most of the Padangnese restaurants around the area.
review 4: Is was First time to try this restaurant and it will be last time. I paid double price for the same food. And the waiter is very rude.
review 5:
Bad experience during late night at simpang ampek waturenggong:
1. Bad attitude of the waiter (smoking)
2. Dirty table
3. Bad taste
4. Unreasonable price (without receipt)

name: warung manado minahasa
address: Gg. XI No.3, Panjer, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80255, Indonesia
review 1:
Literally the best Manado food in denpasar. A secret place, In An ally, super authentic and spectacular food. If you are looking for amazing Indonesian food that you can't get anywhere else around, it's here.

All the food is fresh and very well spiced, with a good variety of dishes available, and the owner Bu Vera is very kind.. My new favorite restaurant
review 2: I only went there once and will never return. The service is so bad. There was only this one woman, I assume she's the owner, because she looked too old to work there, but I'm also not sure because the way she acted didn't seem like she was the owner. When I came to the restaurant, she was busy with her phone and ignored me. When she finally served me, she seemed lazy AF. I wanted to eat the porridge, but she said she didn't know if they still had it. She could've asked the kitchen, but no, she insisted that I ordered something else instead. The whole time I was there, she was busy talking on the phone and laughing so loudly. We cannot pay with cards or QRIS in this restaurant. I didn't have cash, so she told me to transfer to her Dana account. I don't have Dana, so I had to transfer from the bank, but she only gave me her phone number and told me to just Google the virtual account number for Dana. After spending a while trying to pay with Dana, she finally told me she had a bank account. D'oh! So I transferred to her bank account. That was only the bad service. The restaurant itself was so bad, looked filthy, and they played gospel songs in maximum volume the whole time. It was extremely loud. The food was lacking. So many important items like Sambal Dabu and yellow rice weren't available. What kind of Manado restaurant doesn't have Sambal Dabu. Luckily, the food itself was actually really good and cheap. I really love the food, but it's not worth the bad service.
review 3:
This place serve non-halal food.
All of the menu is homecook
review 4: Expensive, the taste not real manado, variant menu only view
review 5: Delicius... good taste.. extra size... and clean place... recomended to TRY...

name: Kona Loka
address: Jl. Waturenggong No.68, Panjer, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80113, Indonesia

review 2: Love Padang-style dishes at Tuah Sakato. They taste really good.
review 3: Like the fried eel and sambal hijau...
